      <title>Veeam Agent for Linux Installation Deep Dive</title>
      <link>https://blog.backupnext.cloud/en/2021/10/veeam-agent-for-linux-installation-deep-dive/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 12 Oct 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>Coku2015@gmail.com (Lei Wei)</author>
      <guid>https://blog.backupnext.cloud/en/2021/10/veeam-agent-for-linux-installation-deep-dive/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-components--roles&#34;&gt;1. Components &amp;amp; Roles&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Veeam Agent for Linux (VAL) has two parts: the &lt;strong&gt;Veeam binaries&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;VeeamSnap kernel module&lt;/strong&gt;. On CentOS/Red Hat, you typically install:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block code-line-numbers open&#34; style=&#34;counter-reset: code-block 0&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-header language-&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;code-title&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;arrow fas fa-angle-right fa-fw&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;ellipses&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-ellipsis-h fa-fw&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;copy&#34; title=&#34;Copy to clipboard&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;far fa-copy fa-fw&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;veeam-&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;.rpm&#xA;veeamsnap-&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;.rpm&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;VeeamSnap handles snapshots and CBT; the Veeam package installs everything else. When you install &lt;code&gt;veeam&lt;/code&gt;, it automatically pulls in &lt;code&gt;veeamsnap&lt;/code&gt; as a dependency.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-installation-path&#34;&gt;2. Installation Path&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;VAL relies on the distro’s package manager to fetch dependencies (see &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.backupnext.cloud/2020/09/Veeam-Linux-Agent-101/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener noreffer &#34;&gt;“Veeam Agent for Linux Basics”&lt;/a&gt;). Push installs from VBR hide the complexity, but special cases exist.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
